Ingredients

125g  Butter (at room temperature)
125g  caster sugar
2     eggs (not straight from fridge)
125g  plain flour
3/4 tspn  baking powder
Some  Milk
3 tbspn  drinking chocolate (or 50g ish? melted chocolate - not cooking chocolate)
200g plain chocolate
200ml double cream

Steps

1 - Place plain chocolate and cream in a saucepan with a little water on a low heat until the chocolate melts
2 - Take saucepan of heat and whisk mixture until smooth, glossy and thickened. Set aside for two hours until thick enough to spread on cake
3 - Mix the butter and sugar into a pasty mess
4 - Crack in the eggs and beat into a slightly gooey pasty mess, (add in melted chocolate at this stage)
5 - Sieve flour and baking powder together. Add to wet ingredients in thirds and fold in after each addition
6 - Sieve drinking chocolate into wet mix and fold all together
7 - Add a little milk until it has a custard-like consistency
8 - Grease a cake tin and line with thing to stop the cake sticking (baking parchment)
9 - Pour cake batter into tin
10 - Cook at 180 degrees C for about 20mins
11 - Place on a rack to cool
12 - Spread icing evenly over cake
13 - Eat
